The paper deals with the complexity of learning Bayesian networks from data, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of oracles for independence, inference, and information, which are related to data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem in terms of information theory, which could place it in cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
